  2. Haggling is. <br>
  3. After drinking good tea, people will get a "dry-sweet" feeling/taste in their throats. According to one tea-grower I talked to, this is from insects eating bits of tea leaves. The only explanation I could think of was that these insects were actually pollinating the leaves, making them slightly sweet.
</p>

